{"parse":{"title":"Pedagogical grammar","pageid":23973415,"revid":816117316,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"vertical-navbox nowraplinks\" style=\"float:right;clear:right;width:22.0em;margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em;background:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em;border-spacing:0.4em 0;text-align:center;line-height:1.4em;font-size:88%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding-top:0.4em;line-height:1.2em\">Part of a series on</td></tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.2em 0.4em 0.2em;padding-top:0;font-size:145%;line-height:1.2em;font-size:200%;font-weight:normal;background:#ddf;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Linguistics\" title=\"Linguistics\">Linguistics</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0.3em 0.4em 0.3em;font-weight:bold;border-top: 1px solid #aaa; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa;padding-bottom:0.35em;\">\n<div class=\"hlist hlist-separated\"><ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Outline_of_linguistics\" title=\"Outline of linguistics\">Outline</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/History_of_linguistics\" title=\"History of linguistics\">History</a></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Index_of_linguistics_articles\" title=\"Index of linguistics articles\">Index</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;background:#ddd;//border-top:1px solid #aaa;text-align:center;\">Subfields</div><div class=\"NavContent hlist\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Language_acquisition\" title=\"Language acquisition\">Acquisition</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Anthropological_linguistics\" title=\"Anthropological linguistics\">Anthropological</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Applied_linguistics\" title=\"Applied linguistics\">Applied</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Computational_linguistics\" title=\"Computational linguistics\">Computational</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Discourse_analysis\" title=\"Discourse analysis\">Discourse analysis</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Forensic_linguistics\" title=\"Forensic linguistics\">Forensic</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Historical_linguistics\" title=\"Historical linguistics\">Historical</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Lexicography\" title=\"Lexicography\">Lexicography</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Morphology_(linguistics)\" title=\"Morphology (linguistics)\">Morphology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Neurolinguistics\" title=\"Neurolinguistics\">Neurolinguistics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Philosophy_of_language\" title=\"Philosophy of language\">Philosophy of language</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Phonetics\" title=\"Phonetics\">Phonetics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Phonology\" title=\"Phonology\">Phonology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Pragmatics\" title=\"Pragmatics\">Pragmatics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Psycholinguistics\" title=\"Psycholinguistics\">Psycholinguistics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Semantics\" title=\"Semantics\">Semantics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sociolinguistics\" title=\"Sociolinguistics\">Sociolinguistics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Syntax\" title=\"Syntax\">Syntax</a></li></ul></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;background:#ddd;//border-top:1px solid #aaa;text-align:center;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Grammar\" title=\"Grammar\">Grammatical Theories</a></div><div class=\"NavContent hlist\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Cognitive_grammar\" title=\"Cognitive grammar\">Cognitive</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Constraint-based_grammar\" title=\"Constraint-based grammar\">Constraint-based</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Dependency_grammar\" title=\"Dependency grammar\">Dependency</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Functional_theories_of_grammar\" title=\"Functional theories of grammar\">Functional</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Generative_grammar\" title=\"Generative grammar\">Generative</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Stochastic_grammar\" title=\"Stochastic grammar\">Stochastic</a></li></ul></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;background:#ddd;//border-top:1px solid #aaa;text-align:center;\">Topics</div><div class=\"NavContent hlist\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Linguistic_description\" title=\"Linguistic description\">Descriptivism</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Etymology\" title=\"Etymology\">Etymology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Internet_linguistics\" title=\"Internet linguistics\">Internet linguistics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/LGBT_linguistics\" title=\"LGBT linguistics\">LGBT linguistics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Linguistic_anthropology\" title=\"Linguistic anthropology\">Linguistic anthropology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Origin_of_language\" title=\"Origin of language\">Origin of language</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Origin_of_speech\" title=\"Origin of speech\">Origin of speech</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Orthography\" title=\"Orthography\">Orthography</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Linguistic_prescription\" title=\"Linguistic prescription\">Prescriptivism</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Second-language_acquisition\" title=\"Second-language acquisition\">Second-language acquisition</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Structural_linguistics\" title=\"Structural linguistics\">Structuralism</a></li></ul></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0.3em 0.4em 0.3em;font-weight:bold;border-top: 1px solid #aaa; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa;background:#ddf;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Linguistics\" title=\"Portal:Linguistics\">Linguistics portal</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding-top: 0.6em;\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Linguistics\" title=\"Template:Linguistics\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Linguistics\" title=\"Template talk:Linguistics\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Linguistics&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>A <b>pedagogical grammar</b> is a modern approach in <a href=\"/wiki/Linguistics\" title=\"Linguistics\">linguistics</a> intended to aid in teaching an additional language.  \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Structure\">Structure</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pedagogical_grammar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Structure\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>This method of teaching is divided into the descriptive: grammatical analysis, and the prescriptive: the articulation of a set of rules. Following an analysis of the context in which it is to be used, one grammatical form or arrangement of words will be determined to be the most appropriate.It helps in learning the grammar of foreign languages.  Pedagogical grammars typically require rules that are definite, coherent, non-technical, cumulative and <a href=\"/wiki/Heuristics\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Heuristics\">heuristic</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> As the rules themselves accumulate, an <a href=\"/wiki/Axiomatic_system\" title=\"Axiomatic system\">axiomatic system</a> is formed between the two languages that should then enable a native speaker of the first to learn the second.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pedagogical_grammar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Odlin, T., (ed.) <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=TbI8AdapFNAC&amp;printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false\">Perspectives on Pedagogical Grammar</a>,</i> (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 1994)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Thomann, J., <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.academia.edu/download/31885265/lfg02thomann-num.pdf\">LFG as a pedagogical grammar</a>,</i> in King, T. and Butt, M. (eds.) 'Proceedings of the LFG02 Conference,' (Stanford: CSLI Publications, 2002)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pedagogical_grammar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Chalker, S. 'Pedagogical grammar: principles and problems,' in Bygate, M. (ed.) <i>Grammar and the Language Teacher,</i> (London: Prentice Hall, 1994)</li>\n<li>Ellis, R. '<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.hpu.edu/Libraries_HPU/Files/TESOL/TQD/VOL_40_1.pdf#page=83\">Current issues in the teaching of grammar: an SLA perspective</a>.' in TESOL Quarterly, 40/1: 83-107.</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2255\nCached time: 20180916034156\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.064 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.079 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 131/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 11390/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 5/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1034/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.016/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 777 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   46.566      1 Template:Linguistics\n100.00%   46.566      1 -total\n 92.89%   43.257      1 Template:Sidebar_with_collapsible_lists\n 21.07%    9.810      1 Template:Hlist\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:23973415-0!canonical and timestamp 20180916034155 and revision id 816117316\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":" ","*":"Grammar"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Language_acquisition"}],"links":[{"ns":10,"exists":"","*":"Template:Linguistics"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Anthropological linguistics"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Applied linguistics"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Axiomatic system"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Cognitive grammar"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Computational linguistics"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Constraint-based grammar"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Dependency grammar"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Discourse analysis"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Etymology"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Forensic linguistics"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Functional theories of grammar"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Generative grammar"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Grammar"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Heuristics"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Historical linguistics"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"History of linguistics"},{"ns":0,"exist